1
00:00:00,510 --> 00:00:04,610
Grandfather died saving me?
What kind of fire was it?

2
00:00:06,480 --> 00:00:09,110
Your real name is Choi Ha Joon.

3
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:10,950
Choi Ha Joon.

4
00:00:13,650 --> 00:00:16,290
(Shareholder Information,
Choi Ha Joon, Ma Dae Chang)

5
00:00:17,320 --> 00:00:19,790
A young punk like him
is the majority shareholder?

6
00:00:22,990 --> 00:00:25,560
"Inferno engulfs residential area
in Sogong-dong, Seoul."

7
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:28,970
"Homeowner dead.
Young grandson dramatically rescued."

8
00:00:29,630 --> 00:00:31,540
"Following a massive fire
of unknown origin..."

9
00:00:31,540 --> 00:00:33,440
"in a residential area of Sogong-dong,"

10
00:00:33,870 --> 00:00:36,540
"homeowner Mr. Choi
saved his young grandson,"

11
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:39,310
"but was unable to escape and died."

12
00:00:39,780 --> 00:00:41,280
"Police and fire authorities..."

13
00:00:41,550 --> 00:00:43,210
"are currently investigating
the exact cause of the fire..."

14
00:00:43,450 --> 00:00:45,220
"and the extent of the property damage."

15
00:00:46,350 --> 00:00:50,320
These articles line up with
what the orphanage director told me.

16
00:00:51,060 --> 00:00:52,060
Then that means...

17
00:01:05,140 --> 00:01:06,870
I was a good student,

18
00:01:07,610 --> 00:01:09,710
so I got into a college prep high school.

19
00:01:10,310 --> 00:01:14,580
My sponsors promised
to send me to college,

20
00:01:15,050 --> 00:01:16,980
so I trusted them and let them adopt me.

21
00:01:17,620 --> 00:01:18,620
But the truth is,

22
00:01:19,520 --> 00:01:21,120
they were monsters.

23
00:01:21,390 --> 00:01:22,390
How terrible.

24
00:01:24,290 --> 00:01:26,390
You must have been through so much.

25
00:01:29,090 --> 00:01:30,090
Alright.

26
00:01:31,230 --> 00:01:32,230
I...

27
00:01:33,600 --> 00:01:35,030
will accept you as my daughter.

28
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:39,300
Thank you, Dad.

29
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,580
But I have a favor to ask of you.

30
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:45,640
A favor?

31
00:01:46,310 --> 00:01:49,610
Please don't publicly announce
that I'm your daughter.

32
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:53,920
Please keep it a secret from Oh Jang Mi
and the rest of the family.

33
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:57,490
Only you and I should know.

34
00:01:58,260 --> 00:02:00,120
Please let's keep things
the way they are now.

35
00:02:01,830 --> 00:02:04,530
Is there a reason?

36
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:08,170
People think Dong Seok and I are married,

37
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:11,570
and they also think we have
a biological daughter, Ma Seo Rin.

38
00:02:12,300 --> 00:02:17,010
Even if you reveal Dong Seok was adopted,
he and I would legally be siblings.

39
00:02:18,010 --> 00:02:19,580
Besides, the whole world knows me...

40
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:23,150
as your daughter-in-law.

41
00:02:23,950 --> 00:02:27,850
People will just see it
as a juicy scandal and condemn us,

42
00:02:28,290 --> 00:02:30,690
and Dream will take a direct hit.

43
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:33,660
It will cause problems
with our investors, too.

44
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:36,960
On top of that, there's Oh Jang Mi
posing as Seo Rin.

45
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,760
If this tangled web
of relationships comes out,

46
00:02:40,570 --> 00:02:42,670
how could anyone possibly
handle the truth?

47
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:48,140
I'm sorry.
I've made things even more complicated.

48
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:50,440
So please, Dad,

49
00:02:50,980 --> 00:02:54,010
don't reveal to the world
that I'm your biological daughter.

50
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:58,420
Let me continue as your daughter-in-law,
just like now,

51
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:02,450
and continue to take care of you,
just like I do now.

52
00:03:04,220 --> 00:03:08,030
I'm so proud of you
for being so thoughtful.

53
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:09,860
Very well.

54
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:14,170
Then we'll do as you've asked.

55
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,570
Thank you, Dad.

56
00:03:19,340 --> 00:03:20,710
Just say it already.

57
00:03:21,070 --> 00:03:25,040
Say you'll reinstate me as CEO,
you old geezer.

58
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:26,210
Also...

59
00:03:27,980 --> 00:03:29,150
First,

60
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:34,020
I will reinstate you as the CEO
of Dream Hotel.

61
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:36,990
Thank you.

62
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:41,190
As your daughter,
and for you and for Dream,

63
00:03:41,730 --> 00:03:44,230
I'll devote my entire life
to working as hard as I can.

64
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:48,130
Chae Hwa Young. Do you really think
I don't know who you are?

65
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:51,900
How dare you try
to pass yourself off as my daughter?

66
00:03:52,640 --> 00:03:53,970
Wretched girl.

67
00:03:56,210 --> 00:03:59,580
Kang Hyuk, I'm Chairman Ma's daughter now.

68
00:03:59,710 --> 00:04:01,110
So, the plan worked?

69
00:04:01,580 --> 00:04:03,050
Of course it did.

70
00:04:03,550 --> 00:04:06,320
All the doors that were closed to us
will finally open.

71
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:10,390
- That's great news.
- Tell me about it.

72
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:13,730
Now I just have to tell Jun Ho.

73
00:04:15,930 --> 00:04:18,000
I'll be there soon. Just wait for me.

74
00:04:20,160 --> 00:04:21,670
Chae Hwa Young.

75
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:26,340
Alright. I'll put you back in charge,

76
00:04:26,940 --> 00:04:29,410
and then expose every last bit
of your corruption.

77
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:33,410
Enjoy it while it lasts.

78
00:04:34,010 --> 00:04:35,150
You witch.

79
00:04:36,350 --> 00:04:38,750
How dare she impersonate my daughter?

80
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:46,360
- You called for me, Chairman?
- I did.

81
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:50,060
Chae Hwa Young is not my daughter.

82
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:51,860
What?

83
00:04:53,130 --> 00:04:55,330
To think she tried to fool me with this.

84
00:04:57,970 --> 00:04:59,100
But you know what?

85
00:04:59,670 --> 00:05:03,740
I'm certain that Chae Hwa Young
knows who my daughter is.

86
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:06,240
So for now, let's pretend to fall for it.

87
00:05:06,810 --> 00:05:09,250
We'll use Chae Hwa Young
to find my real daughter.

88
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:11,680
Yes, I understand.

89
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:14,950
But the DNA test...

90
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:18,890
Chae Hwa Young
could easily fake something like that.

91
00:05:20,190 --> 00:05:23,590
How dare she!
Did she really think she could fool me?

92
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:29,470
Baek Ho.

93
00:05:32,300 --> 00:05:34,170
Did you get to meet the director?

94
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:38,040
He said my name is Choi Ha Joon.

95
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,040
Choi Ha Joon.

96
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:42,150
So, your birth name is Choi Ha Joon.

97
00:05:43,580 --> 00:05:45,520
Then what about your parents?

98
00:05:45,650 --> 00:05:50,420
Apparently, my parents died in a car crash
shortly after I was born,

99
00:05:50,820 --> 00:05:53,560
and I was raised by my grandfather.
I also had a nanny.

100
00:05:54,490 --> 00:05:58,830
I suspected as much.
So you really were from a wealthy family.

101
00:06:00,470 --> 00:06:03,740
But then why did you end up
at the orphanage?

102
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:05,470
The director wasn't sure
about that either.

103
00:06:06,340 --> 00:06:10,340
He said a woman dropped me off,
claiming to be my nanny.

104
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:12,610
When the director kept pressing her
for details,

105
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,310
she ran off while filling out the form.

106
00:06:15,310 --> 00:06:17,050
Really?

107
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:23,150
And what's this?

108
00:06:23,690 --> 00:06:26,890
It seems my grandfather saved me...

109
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:28,960
and died in a fire.

110
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,500
- How awful.
- I think this is the article.

111
00:06:32,960 --> 00:06:36,230
The name in this article is Choi,
and it says he saved his young grandson.

112
00:06:36,570 --> 00:06:40,910
My goodness.
What a terribly tragic incident.

113
00:06:42,170 --> 00:06:45,310
So there's a good chance
this man was your grandfather, then?

114
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:46,910
Yes.

115
00:06:47,610 --> 00:06:50,280
Sogong-dong is
a pretty wealthy neighborhood.

116
00:06:50,880 --> 00:06:52,220
How could a fire have started there?

117
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:56,120
Mom, I have to find out
why my grandfather died.

118
00:06:56,650 --> 00:07:01,290
The reason I ended up at the orphanage
must be connected to this fire.

119
00:07:01,790 --> 00:07:03,590
I need to find out
my grandfather's full name for sure, too.

120
00:07:03,830 --> 00:07:07,870
First, let's pull the old property records
for this address.

121
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:10,940
That should tell you
your grandfather's full name.

122
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:12,500
Right.

123
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,410
My last name is Choi,

124
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:19,480
so why do I have the Ma family crest?

125
00:07:21,580 --> 00:07:22,810
So, you're telling me CEO Chae...

126
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:26,450
tried to acquire Hills Hotel
behind my back with her slush fund,

127
00:07:26,450 --> 00:07:27,820
and failed?

128
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,820
And it appears Director Ma
was also involved.

129
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,720
That reminds me...

130
00:07:33,260 --> 00:07:36,690
The other day, when Seo Rin's building
was put up as collateral,

131
00:07:37,030 --> 00:07:39,060
but the debt was paid off right away.

132
00:07:40,570 --> 00:07:43,500
So Jang Mi was connected
to this after all.

133
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:49,570
Yes. And the 30 million dollars withdrawn
from Chae Hwa Young's Swiss account...

134
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:51,640
ended up in Director Ma's account.

135
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:54,380
My Jang Mi...

136
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,280
took away Chae Hwa Young's slush fund.

137
00:07:59,480 --> 00:08:02,190
She's improving by leaps and bounds.

138
00:08:02,190 --> 00:08:03,390
Just as I expected...

139
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:06,160
from my granddaughter.

140
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,700
CEO Chae
is Chairman Ma's biological daughter?

141
00:08:11,630 --> 00:08:14,400
- Ridiculous! What are you talking about?
- The two of them...

142
00:08:14,770 --> 00:08:16,570
even had a DNA test done.

143
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,240
It's certain.

144
00:08:18,300 --> 00:08:20,400
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

145
00:08:21,370 --> 00:08:22,570
I refuse to believe it.

146
00:08:23,240 --> 00:08:26,710
Whatever you and CEO Chae are up to now,

147
00:08:26,710 --> 00:08:28,110
just keep me out of it.

148
00:08:28,550 --> 00:08:29,910
I'm so sick of it.

149
00:08:36,750 --> 00:08:39,720
Anyway, I don't care what's going on
with you two.

150
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:42,990
What I want to ask you about
is Choi Ha Joon.

151
00:08:43,790 --> 00:08:44,800
Choi Ha Joon?

152
00:08:45,330 --> 00:08:46,400
This majority shareholder here...

153
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,970
Choi Ha Joon. Who is he?

154
00:08:49,600 --> 00:08:50,600
Well...

155
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:52,370
I don't know.

156
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,700
You don't know?

157
00:08:55,710 --> 00:08:56,740
Really?

158
00:08:57,810 --> 00:08:59,040
Then I'll have you look into him.

159
00:08:59,780 --> 00:09:02,080
Choi Ha Joon, born in 1993.

160
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,550
Find out how much he's worth,

161
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:07,520
his recent whereabouts,
and who he's connected to.

162
00:09:07,850 --> 00:09:09,020
Dig up everything you can on him.

163
00:09:09,450 --> 00:09:10,520
And if I find all that out,

164
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,920
what are you planning to do?

165
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:15,430
He's the solution for the money
we blew on Hills Hotel.

166
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,300
If we can just get
Choi Ha Joon on our side,

167
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,530
we'll more than make up for our losses
in one fell swoop.

168
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:23,070
Choi Ha Joon?

169
00:09:23,430 --> 00:09:25,400
Who is this Choi Ha Joon
that he's so determined to win over?

170
00:09:25,770 --> 00:09:30,240
(General Manager's Office)

171
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:35,680
Yes, Grandfather.

172
00:09:36,580 --> 00:09:37,580
What?

173
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:39,950
So you're reinstating
Chae Hwa Young as CEO,

174
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:42,150
and you want me to get the CEO's office
all set up for her?

175
00:09:43,050 --> 00:09:44,760
Wait, what's going on all of a sudden?

176
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:48,430
We can't just let CEO Chae's talent
go to waste, can we?

177
00:09:48,530 --> 00:09:52,400
But Baek Ho and I are working so hard
to gather evidence of her crimes.

178
00:09:52,660 --> 00:09:53,860
If you make her the CEO again,

179
00:09:54,170 --> 00:09:56,970
you'll stop us to protect the company,
like you did last time.

180
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,670
Hey, I said it's just for the time being.

181
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:04,980
If you chop down a tree carelessly,
you can ruin the entire forest, you know.

182
00:10:09,050 --> 00:10:10,450
What in the world is going on?

183
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:15,120
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

184
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:25,130
Ma'am, where are you?

185
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,500
Kang Hyuk.

186
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:32,570
Kang Hyuk, it worked.
It finally all came together.

187
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:37,980
I'm finally back as the CEO.

188
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,310
I'm finally back in my office.

189
00:10:40,810 --> 00:10:42,550
What should I do first?

190
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:45,520
Kang Hyuk, how can I even express
how happy I am?

191
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:46,850
Congratulations.

192
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:53,460
Right. Why did you call me?

193
00:10:54,190 --> 00:10:55,360
Oh, right.

194
00:10:55,560 --> 00:10:58,430
General Manager Kang told me
to look into Choi Ha Joon.

195
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:01,530
You mean Choi Ha Joon,
the largest shareholder?

196
00:11:11,010 --> 00:11:14,050
Does CEO Chae by any chance
have a golden toad?

197
00:11:25,560 --> 00:11:27,960
Why did Kang Baek Ho suddenly
ask about this?

198
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:30,560
Chairman Ma said...

199
00:11:31,130 --> 00:11:33,900
when CEO Chae was pregnant with her son,

200
00:11:34,130 --> 00:11:36,300
he sent her a golden toad as a gift.

201
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,570
He said it's engraved
with his family's unique crest.

202
00:11:41,140 --> 00:11:42,410
(Ma)

203
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,410
Is this...

204
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:45,980
the Chairman's family crest?

205
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:52,580
Baek Ho and CEO Chae
have the same grapefruit allergy.

206
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:56,350
Does that mean Baek Ho is CEO Chae's son?

207
00:12:04,930 --> 00:12:06,430
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

208
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:09,030
Jun Ho, you've heard the good news,
haven't you?

209
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,470
About how I'm the Chairman's daughter now.

210
00:12:11,770 --> 00:12:13,740
Stop with that ridiculous nonsense.

211
00:12:13,970 --> 00:12:14,970
Be quiet.

212
00:12:15,540 --> 00:12:16,540
Quiet.

213
00:12:17,270 --> 00:12:20,280
Anyway, this means your marriage
to Oh Jang Mi is off the table.

214
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:21,980
So don't even dream about it.

215
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:25,480
- What did you say?
- I'm Ma Eun Hye, the Chairman's daughter.

216
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:27,850
That makes you and Oh Jang Mi cousins.

217
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,090
So how could you two possibly get married?

218
00:12:30,390 --> 00:12:32,960
Your lie is exposed
the second Oh Jang Mi runs...

219
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:34,160
a DNA test on the Chairman and me.

220
00:12:34,890 --> 00:12:37,860
- Why would you do something so reckless?
- To buy time.

221
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:42,970
The only thing in your brilliant head
is marrying Oh Jang Mi, isn't it?

222
00:12:43,830 --> 00:12:46,240
In a situation like this,
we should be using this chance...

223
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,310
to figure out how
we can siphon money out of Dream...

224
00:12:48,710 --> 00:12:50,940
and how to get our hands on the shares.

225
00:12:50,940 --> 00:12:52,480
That's what we should be calculating.

226
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,610
- Understand?
- So you'd pull a risky stunt for that?

227
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:58,420
How much more are you going
to get in my way?

228
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:01,420
- General Manager Kang.
- So I should just do nothing,

229
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:04,860
and wait to get thrown out
when the Chairman finds Ma Eun Hye?

230
00:13:05,090 --> 00:13:06,490
Is that what you want?

231
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:11,660
We have to buy time before the Chairman
actually finds Ma Eun Hye.

232
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:15,300
I'm going crazy over
losing my precious 30 million dollars.

233
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:17,270
We have to find a way to turn this around.

234
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:18,700
Fine.

235
00:13:20,300 --> 00:13:21,310
Let me ask you one thing.

236
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:26,240
You once told me you lost your child
because of Jang Mi's mother, right?

237
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,080
- Jun Ho, that's...
- What?

238
00:13:29,080 --> 00:13:30,350
Is that child alive?

239
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:32,380
What are you talking about?

240
00:13:32,980 --> 00:13:36,790
- Why bring up that child?
- Baek Ho has the golden toad.

241
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:39,290
And Baek Ho was adopted, too.

242
00:13:39,790 --> 00:13:42,490
- What?
- The golden toad that Baek Ho has...

243
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:44,460
a crest engraved on it.

244
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:49,170
The Chairman gave out two golden toads.

245
00:13:49,830 --> 00:13:51,200
They were stamped with the family crest.

246
00:13:51,540 --> 00:13:53,240
Baek Ho has one of them.

247
00:13:53,840 --> 00:13:56,510
And Baek Ho
has the same grapefruit allergy as you.

248
00:13:57,070 --> 00:13:58,810
What do you make of that?

249
00:13:58,810 --> 00:14:00,010
That's impossible.

250
00:14:00,710 --> 00:14:02,680
Kang Baek Ho has a grapefruit
allergy, too?

251
00:14:02,750 --> 00:14:05,080
Baek Ho can't be your son,

252
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,250
right?

253
00:14:09,050 --> 00:14:10,250
He can't be, can he?

254
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:14,660
That's impossible.

255
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:16,990
No, that child is dead.

256
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,400
He's definitely dead.

257
00:14:22,900 --> 00:14:26,640
What? The Chairman reinstated
Chae Hwa Young as the CEO?

258
00:14:26,840 --> 00:14:28,010
What are you talking about?

259
00:14:28,710 --> 00:14:29,840
That's ridiculous.

260
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:32,040
Has the Chairman gone senile or something?

261
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:35,110
- Why would he do that?
- Did he have some change of heart?

262
00:14:35,650 --> 00:14:38,750
Or maybe Chae Hwa Young
is up to something.

263
00:14:38,980 --> 00:14:39,980
Tell me about it.

264
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:43,190
I can't just listen to this.
I'll see him first thing tomorrow.

265
00:14:43,390 --> 00:14:46,060
Okay, Mom.
I'll give Grandfather a heads-up.

266
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,730
You need to be careful, ma'am.

267
00:14:47,990 --> 00:14:50,060
You never know.
Chae Hwa Young might try to harm you.

268
00:14:50,230 --> 00:14:52,330
Okay, don't worry, Baek Ho.

269
00:14:54,270 --> 00:14:55,970
My Eun Hye...

270
00:14:57,270 --> 00:14:59,100
Where am I supposed to find her?

271
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,740
Seong Hye. It's been a while.
How have you been?

272
00:15:08,410 --> 00:15:12,180
Hey, you called me the other day saying
you had something to tell me.

273
00:15:12,550 --> 00:15:16,190
To be honest, I couldn't bring myself
to tell you this last time,

274
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:19,190
and I've felt uneasy...

275
00:15:19,190 --> 00:15:20,920
since I only told this
to your daughter-in-law, CEO Chae.

276
00:15:21,030 --> 00:15:22,130
To CEO Chae?

277
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:25,360
What did you say to her?

278
00:15:25,730 --> 00:15:27,260
The thing is...

279
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,500
- I'm sure it will smell awful.
- I didn't do it!

280
00:15:36,410 --> 00:15:38,780
That's a habit my sister had.

281
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:44,180
Wait, is that really true?

282
00:15:44,820 --> 00:15:47,550
You're saying Jang Mi's mother did that?

283
00:15:47,790 --> 00:15:51,090
Yes. It could've just been
a random gesture,

284
00:15:51,390 --> 00:15:52,990
but for some reason,
after seeing her do that,

285
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:55,630
she seemed to take after my sister,
Seong Sil.

286
00:15:55,860 --> 00:15:58,630
I told CEO Chae first...

287
00:15:58,630 --> 00:16:00,860
because I didn't want
to shock you too much,

288
00:16:01,230 --> 00:16:03,570
but I felt you needed to know as well.

289
00:16:06,140 --> 00:16:07,140
Goodness, it's hot!

290
00:16:09,740 --> 00:16:11,240
So you're saying...

291
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:14,140
you only told CEO Chae?

292
00:16:15,010 --> 00:16:16,010
Yes.

293
00:16:16,450 --> 00:16:19,650
It's a weight off my shoulders
now that I've told you myself.

294
00:16:20,420 --> 00:16:22,950
Right, you did the right thing.

295
00:16:23,520 --> 00:16:26,360
Okay, take care now.

296
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:31,460
Chae Hwa Young.

297
00:16:31,860 --> 00:16:33,660
I knew you’d do that.

298
00:16:35,030 --> 00:16:39,600
You knew about Seong Sil's habit
from the very beginning, didn't you?

299
00:16:41,970 --> 00:16:44,210
If I get my hands on that witch
and break her,

300
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,410
will she confess...

301
00:16:48,380 --> 00:16:49,410
where my real daughter is?

302
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:52,080
No.

303
00:16:53,120 --> 00:16:56,950
If I do that,
my real daughter could be in danger.

304
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,860
Wait.

305
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:03,560
Jung Suk Hee...

306
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:07,770
has the same habit as Seong Sil?

307
00:17:12,270 --> 00:17:14,140
Are you absolutely sure
that child is dead?

308
00:17:14,710 --> 00:17:17,980
Yes, ma'am. He died at the hospital.
I confirmed it myself.

309
00:17:18,410 --> 00:17:20,910
Right? So my child is really dead?

310
00:17:20,980 --> 00:17:22,050
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

311
00:17:22,080 --> 00:17:25,020
Why did Jun Ho have to give me
a heart attack for no reason?

312
00:17:25,820 --> 00:17:26,950
Hold on.

313
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:29,190
If Kang Baek Ho was adopted,

314
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,390
then the owner of the golden toad...

315
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:33,290
must be his birth parents.

316
00:17:34,290 --> 00:17:36,060
Does that mean he's related
to Chairman Ma's family?

317
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,730
There are only a few people
in Chairman Ma's family.

318
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:41,370
And the ones who passed away
died without any heirs.

319
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:42,770
Is that right?

320
00:17:43,570 --> 00:17:47,140
I have enough problems already.
Why does Kang Baek Ho make me so uneasy?

321
00:17:48,540 --> 00:17:51,740
In any case, we should look into
Kang Baek Ho's background.

322
00:17:52,380 --> 00:17:54,480
If he turns out to be connected
to Chairman Ma,

323
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:57,050
he'll be a major problem for us.

324
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:01,050
Manager Lee, I want you to start digging
into Kang Baek Ho's past immediately.

325
00:18:01,250 --> 00:18:04,120
The infant home he was at, or whatever.

326
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:05,420
Search everything.

327
00:18:05,660 --> 00:18:07,620
Find out what family he comes from.

328
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:09,960
Yes, ma'am.

329
00:18:20,870 --> 00:18:23,210
Thief! Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

330
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:26,510
Are you insane?

331
00:18:26,510 --> 00:18:28,150
How dare you call me a thief?

332
00:18:28,410 --> 00:18:29,650
Why are you back again?

333
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:31,650
I haven’t seen you in a while here.
What brings you here?

334
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:32,950
Why are you back now?

335
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,250
I'm sick to death of seeing your face.

336
00:18:35,590 --> 00:18:36,720
Get out of here, now!

337
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:38,990
This is Grandfather's house.

338
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:40,420
It's my Jang Mi's house.

339
00:18:41,630 --> 00:18:43,190
"Jang Mi's house," my foot.

340
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,700
Chae Hwa Young is a thief.

341
00:18:46,230 --> 00:18:47,930
A baby stealer.

342
00:18:48,570 --> 00:18:50,870
You'll be punished.
May the sky strike you down!

343
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:53,000
If you go mad,
at least do it with dignity.

344
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:55,140
- You crazy fool, why would you...
- What is all this commotion?

345
00:18:57,810 --> 00:19:01,480
How can you just walk in here
covered in all that dust?

346
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,210
Get away from me, thief!

347
00:19:03,210 --> 00:19:06,280
CEO Chae,
don't you have a breakfast meeting?

348
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:10,250
- You should get going.
- Yes. I'll be on my way, Father.

349
00:19:17,530 --> 00:19:22,000
I thought Chae Hwa Young would be a mess
after losing 30 million dollars,

350
00:19:22,470 --> 00:19:24,640
but why is she so full of life?

351
00:19:25,540 --> 00:19:27,700
What on earth is she plotting?

352
00:19:32,140 --> 00:19:34,850
What's this? It looks very healthy.

353
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:37,280
It's an abalone and mushroom stew
with perilla seeds.

354
00:19:37,580 --> 00:19:41,120
Mom made it specially for Grandfather
because of his high blood pressure.

355
00:19:41,620 --> 00:19:43,090
Goodness, it's hot!

356
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:54,970
Seriously, how could Manager Lee
be so incompetent?

357
00:19:55,100 --> 00:19:57,400
The breakfast meeting is tomorrow,
but he thought it was today.

358
00:19:58,370 --> 00:19:59,970
I dressed in these uncomfortable clothes
for nothing.

359
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:02,140
Suk Hee is a good cook.

360
00:20:02,140 --> 00:20:03,970
Suk Hee made it delicious.

361
00:20:04,470 --> 00:20:07,080
What? Is she still here?

362
00:20:07,950 --> 00:20:08,950
I ought to...

363
00:20:16,450 --> 00:20:18,060
(Chang)

364
00:20:18,320 --> 00:20:19,320
My necklace!

365
00:20:21,590 --> 00:20:22,760
What are you doing?

366
00:20:24,630 --> 00:20:26,160
- That hurts!
- Mom!

367
00:20:27,230 --> 00:20:28,930
Mom.

368
00:20:29,430 --> 00:20:31,100
What do you think you're doing?

369
00:20:31,100 --> 00:20:33,340
This woman stole my necklace!

370
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:34,840
Where did you get this?

371
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:40,040
It's a pretty close match.

372
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:42,150
This one is clearly just a copy.

373
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:44,110
It is fake, so that makes sense.

374
00:20:44,950 --> 00:20:47,280
The "Chang" character looks the same
at first glance,

375
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,420
but it is definitely a little different.

376
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:52,060
Goodness.

377
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:55,630
What should I do? This is the fake one.

378
00:20:56,360 --> 00:20:59,860
I completely forgot and just assumed
Jung Suk Hee had stolen my necklace.

379
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,530
What do I do now?

380
00:21:01,530 --> 00:21:04,430
It hurts. My neck is stinging.

381
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:07,870
Go on, hurry and get her treated.

382
00:21:09,210 --> 00:21:12,310
Why did you attack my mom?
She didn't do anything!

383
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:13,880
What did she even do?

384
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:15,950
Give her necklace back.

385
00:21:16,180 --> 00:21:19,380
No way. Chairman Ma can't see this.

386
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:22,620
Give it back now.
It belonged to my late father.

387
00:21:22,690 --> 00:21:25,590
Seriously, Chae Hwa Young,
what are you doing? This is so childish.

388
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:27,520
You snatched the necklace,
but why are you refusing to return it?

389
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:29,160
Hurry and give it back to her.

390
00:21:29,290 --> 00:21:32,900
- Why are you clutching it like that?
- It's mine! It's my necklace!

391
00:21:33,460 --> 00:21:36,100
Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

392
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:38,000
Give it back now!

393
00:21:42,110 --> 00:21:44,940
Go treat her wound.
I'll come check on her later.

394
00:21:45,680 --> 00:21:46,680
I'm sorry.

395
00:21:47,040 --> 00:21:48,410
I misunderstood.

396
00:21:48,410 --> 00:21:49,450
Hey.

397
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:50,980
I need to have a word with you.

398
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:55,250
Why did she even bring the fake
and start all this?

399
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:57,020
This is driving me crazy.

400
00:21:57,820 --> 00:21:59,060
What am I going to tell him?

401
00:22:06,460 --> 00:22:07,700
About that necklace...

402
00:22:08,500 --> 00:22:09,670
What was that all about?

403
00:22:11,940 --> 00:22:13,470
Did you know about it?

404
00:22:14,810 --> 00:22:17,840
Father, I had no idea.

405
00:22:18,510 --> 00:22:20,240
It looked exactly like my necklace,

406
00:22:21,280 --> 00:22:23,980
and since Jung Suk Hee was rummaging
through my room the other day,

407
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,550
I jumped to a conclusion.

408
00:22:25,880 --> 00:22:28,050
That's why I thought
she had stolen my necklace.

409
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:30,920
But we put the necklace...

410
00:22:31,960 --> 00:22:36,190
inside my bible for safekeeping
after we matched the pieces, remember?

411
00:22:36,460 --> 00:22:37,560
Have you forgotten that?

412
00:22:38,260 --> 00:22:39,330
That's right.

413
00:22:39,660 --> 00:22:42,130
It must have slipped my mind.
I only saw the necklace.

414
00:22:42,370 --> 00:22:45,800
I designed and commissioned
that necklace myself.

415
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:50,140
Park Young Mi, the woman
who impersonated Eun Hye,

416
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:53,910
said she copied your necklace
to make hers.

417
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,350
But Jung Suk Hee's necklace just now...

418
00:22:56,610 --> 00:22:59,120
looked incredibly similar
to the one I designed.

419
00:22:59,450 --> 00:23:01,850
They're similar, and not identical.

420
00:23:01,850 --> 00:23:03,590
They're completely different, Dad.

421
00:23:04,650 --> 00:23:05,660
Even so,

422
00:23:06,390 --> 00:23:07,790
you're the one who made the mistake,

423
00:23:08,430 --> 00:23:09,730
so go and apologize to her.

424
00:23:10,460 --> 00:23:13,730
It looked like the necklace cut her neck.

425
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:17,070
And in the future,
I don't care how desperate you are,

426
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:18,640
don't you ever make a mistake
like that again.

427
00:23:19,270 --> 00:23:22,740
What kind of behavior is that for a CEO?
You looked undignified.

428
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:26,280
- Do you understand?
- Yes. I'm sorry.

429
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:28,450
I’m going to teach them a lesson.

430
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:32,080
The necklace...

431
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:35,990
So she claims she mistook
Jung Suk Hee's necklace for hers.

432
00:23:36,950 --> 00:23:38,420
Then could Jung Suk Hee be...

433
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:42,530
No, that's impossible.

434
00:23:46,500 --> 00:23:50,400
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine. I was just startled.

435
00:23:50,800 --> 00:23:52,600
What happened to my necklace?

436
00:23:54,470 --> 00:23:57,010
It broke because of Chae Hwa Young.

437
00:23:58,440 --> 00:24:02,410
But is my necklace and Chae Hwa Young's
really identical?

438
00:24:03,210 --> 00:24:04,850
Chae Hwa Young seemed so shocked.

439
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:08,790
- I wonder why.
- I know. What was that about?

440
00:24:13,790 --> 00:24:14,790
Are you okay?

441
00:24:14,860 --> 00:24:17,160
Why on earth did you try
to snatch my mom's necklace?

442
00:24:17,390 --> 00:24:21,200
It looked like mine, so I thought
she went into my room and stole it again.

443
00:24:21,630 --> 00:24:22,970
But on second look, they're different.

444
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:26,440
Suk Hee doesn't go into your room
to steal. That's no fun.

445
00:24:26,500 --> 00:24:29,210
That's right.
Don't ever go into that room.

446
00:24:29,540 --> 00:24:31,580
Otherwise, you might get hurt again
just like today.

447
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:33,240
Give her a real apology.

448
00:24:33,510 --> 00:24:35,250
My mom got hurt because of you.

449
00:24:35,250 --> 00:24:36,510
It's barely a scratch.

450
00:24:37,080 --> 00:24:38,980
So just stop wearing that necklace.

451
00:24:39,280 --> 00:24:41,990
I hate it when people wear things
that look like mine.

452
00:24:42,490 --> 00:24:43,750
If you're going to work here,

453
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:46,960
you should at least be aware
of the master family's tastes.

454
00:24:47,390 --> 00:24:48,390
Don't you think?

455
00:24:49,860 --> 00:24:52,730
What century are you living in?
Who are you calling "the master family"?

456
00:24:53,460 --> 00:24:55,630
She acts like she actually owns the place.

457
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,310
That was a close call.

458
00:25:02,940 --> 00:25:05,640
I thought that little tramp
took the necklace from my room...

459
00:25:05,910 --> 00:25:08,550
and was wearing it as if it were her own.

460
00:25:09,780 --> 00:25:11,180
I really need to be more careful.

461
00:25:12,220 --> 00:25:14,920
But Chairman Ma won't get suspicious,
will he?

462
00:25:16,790 --> 00:25:20,320
Who? Choi Ha Joon?
You want to know what I know about him?

463
00:25:22,090 --> 00:25:24,790
You mean Choi Ha Joon,
the majority shareholder, right?

464
00:25:26,130 --> 00:25:27,130
Yes.

465
00:25:27,530 --> 00:25:30,700
Just that he's never once shown his face
at a stockholders' meeting.

466
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,070
- What else?
- Right.

467
00:25:34,170 --> 00:25:37,140
They say the Chairman's decisions
are Choi Ha Joon's decisions.

468
00:25:37,340 --> 00:25:40,280
I think I heard the directors gossiping
about something like that.

469
00:25:40,410 --> 00:25:43,980
The Chairman's decisions
are Choi Ha Joon's decisions?

470
00:25:44,410 --> 00:25:46,850
But why the sudden interest
in Choi Ha Joon?

471
00:25:54,020 --> 00:25:55,290
Team Leader Jin, you're here too.

472
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:57,660
Could you give us a minute?

473
00:25:58,030 --> 00:25:59,030
Of course.

474
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,700
Do you want me to dig a little deeper
on Choi Ha Joon?

475
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:03,030
That would be great.

476
00:26:04,900 --> 00:26:07,900
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

477
00:26:11,940 --> 00:26:12,940
Choi Ha Joon?

478
00:26:13,640 --> 00:26:15,180
Dream Hotel's majority shareholder.

479
00:26:15,780 --> 00:26:17,580
Why the sudden interest in finding him?

480
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:20,280
I've found a solution
for blowing the Hills Hotel deal.

481
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:23,390
Choi Ha Joon,
the majority shareholder of Dream Hotel.

482
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:26,060
If we can win him over,

483
00:26:26,690 --> 00:26:28,890
we'll easily cover
the 30 million dollar loss.

484
00:26:28,890 --> 00:26:29,890
Jun Ho.

485
00:26:30,260 --> 00:26:33,860
The Hills Hotel deal wasn't your fault,
so why are you stressing over it?

486
00:26:34,260 --> 00:26:35,500
You don't have to be.

487
00:26:35,500 --> 00:26:36,630
The 30 million dollar loss?

488
00:26:37,330 --> 00:26:38,770
Why should you be the one
to worry about it?

489
00:26:39,440 --> 00:26:40,440
Don't worry.

490
00:26:41,100 --> 00:26:44,040
It's only a matter of time
before Dream is in the palm of our hands.

491
00:26:49,310 --> 00:26:51,010
Are you drawing?

492
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:53,050
Yes, Grandfather.

493
00:26:55,090 --> 00:26:59,390
This is Aunt Jang Mi, and this is my mom.
And this is Uncle Tae Pyung.

494
00:26:59,590 --> 00:27:01,590
And this is my grandma.

495
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:02,990
Is that right?

496
00:27:03,130 --> 00:27:05,100
You're a good artist.

497
00:27:05,630 --> 00:27:07,360
You've got real talent.

498
00:27:13,100 --> 00:27:16,110
Who drew this one?
Did you draw this one too, Bo Ra?

499
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:20,680
Yes. My grandma is really good
at making four-leaf clover bracelets.

500
00:27:20,810 --> 00:27:23,380
And she's great
at embroidering handkerchiefs.

501
00:27:23,780 --> 00:27:27,250
I saw her embroidery,
and then I drew this.

502
00:27:28,490 --> 00:27:31,290
- Your grandma?
- Yes, her name is Jung Suk Hee.

503
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:34,920
You don't even know my grandma's name,
Grandfather.

504
00:27:36,190 --> 00:27:37,290
I suppose I don't.

505
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:15,800
(The First Man)

